<br>
Well, I must say... the fear/resist disciplines dont do much at all.  They have a very short duration and an extremely long reuse time (55+mins)  I used the fear discipline on Woushi the other day, and yes, it worked for like 10 seconds, which of course, allowed me to be the only one standing at his feet getting clawed for 520 damage.  Lesson learned, next time use it in conjuction with DA.  <br>
<br>
However, by the time it wore off, Woushi was barely at 60% and I soon found my self wracked with pain and and heading up the face of some mountain wall with woushi clawing at my backside.  OUCH!<br>
<br>
These do have their applications, but need the effect lengthened.<br>
<br>
Holyforge:<br>
<br>
After only using it one time, I really like this ability, and after today's patch I am sure I will like it even more.  My second ever crit as a Paladin was for (209) 230 damage and I about flipped.  It is obvious that it will slightly enhance our capabilities, and I like the fact that others can now see we are actually putting out some damage.  The only issue I seen with it seems to have been enhanced with todays patch.  I only crit'ed (sp?) 2x during my one use of the discipline, it would be nice if it were 10-15 seconds of ALL crits like the warriors get.<br>
<br>
Divine Purpose:<br>
<br>
This is a very good spell.  converts hps at 11hps/tick sitting for me and when coupled with other regens, it can't be beat, very good addition/enhancement for Paladins.  Only costs one (1) mana to casts as well<br>
<br>
Other spells/enhancements:<br>
<br>
Piercing skill was a nice addition, not sure why we didnt have it all along though.  I dont think of piercers as being mega damage weapons in anyone hands but rogues, so I am not sure how it will help us that much.  I can see it making us more diversified, and preventing an environment where everyone has to get the same uber weapon to be as effective in putting out damage.  No complaints really on this skill, purely an addition.<br>
<br>
The group heal spell looks very promising.  Overall, I like the emphasis Verant has put on the healing (WIS) aspects of Paladins.  I hope it makes a few Paladins realize they can do more than just take hits.  I personally am working on having a full set of WIS gear that takes me to 200+WIS, as being able to SH, Group heal, and Rez will make us more competitive in competition for spots in the absence of &quot;those other classes&quot;.<br>
<br>
Overall, I think the new additions have enhanced our class in the eyes of other classes and make us more balanced in respect to not focusing specifically on how much damage we can put out/take as well as being a liability for healing, etc. <p>Qualtar Shylok --

